        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 4:48PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hartville, or 24 miles northeast of Wheatland, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Register Cliff State Historic Site, Jay Em, Guernsey, Oregon Trail
Ruts State Historic Site, Guernsey State Park, and Hartville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
